0; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:103.5pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">What</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">DoTheyK</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">now</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:94.75pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">100-200,000</span></p></td></tr></table></div><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Explaining why interest appears low</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> for the spending data</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> is complex. However, survey respondents and interviewees offered a number of explanations. First, the way in which information was displayed is problematic. As one put it ‘a long list of every invoice over £500 is meaningless to most people’. The information was not contextualised or </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">attached to a narrative ‘a one line showing £x for product/service "Y" is of little use in understanding public expenditure’. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ites</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> in the table above are different. For example,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Police.uk</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> hold</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> specific and relevant information down to the street level. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">TheyWorkForYou</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, which has had considerable success in attracting a wide variety of those not previously participating in politics, offers an easy, user friendly way of understanding the activities of individual MPs</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref15"></a><a href="#_ftn15">[15]</a></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Second it may also not fit with habits: ‘People prefer to send an email rather than look for the information themselves’. They may lack both the ‘skills and time to analyse the data’.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Third, as with all forms of participation, the motivation of the public is likely to be the key barrier. As one respondent put it ‘I assume that most people are not the slightest bit interested in spending their spare time poring over this type of material’. A number felt the lack of interest ‘reflects the general public interest (or lack of interest) in local government’.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Users of the Data </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The table below is drawn from the survey. Officials were asked which group </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">were the primary users</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> of the data published by local authorities.</span></p><div style="text-align:center"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin:0 auto"><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:154pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Primary Users</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:89.75pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Number </span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:154pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Public</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:89.75pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">16</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:154pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Media </span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:89.75pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">18</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:154pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Business</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:89.75pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">24</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:154pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">NGOs</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:89.75pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">3</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:154pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Other</span><a name="_ftnref16"></a><a href="#_ftn16">[16]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:89.75pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">22</span></p></td></tr></table></div><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Public</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">6.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The public were intended to be the beneficiaries of the data but were not often named as the biggest users. This may because of the general barriers to participation outlined above. It may also be connected to where the interest of the public lies. Interviewees pointed out that general ‘engagement’ with local government concerned ‘problems’ or daily matters rather than spending. One Metropolitan Borough Council publishes the number of visits per month to various parts of its website. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">These</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> are the findings for January 2012: </span></p><div style="text-align:center"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin:0 auto"><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:107.25pt"><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Topic of page</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:100.45pt"><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Visits per month</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:107.25pt"><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Planning</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:100.45pt"><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">                    3349</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:107.25pt"><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Bin collections</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:100.45pt"><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">                    3694</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:107.25pt"><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Council Tax</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:100.45pt"><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">                    2009</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:107.25pt"><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Council </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Chamber</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:100.45pt"><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">                    1708</span></p></td></tr><tr style="height:22.65pt"><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:107.25pt"><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Transparency </span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:100.45pt"><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">                       126</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:107.25pt"><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Procurement</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:100.45pt"><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">                        88</span></p></td></tr></table></div><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Media</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">6.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Given the controversy over FOI use by journalists, one possibility was that the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">new d</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ata would be </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">similarly </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">used by the media to hold authorities to account. Authorities reported a ‘flurry’ of interest from journalists but one that often died down. A search o</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">f</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> regional newspapers found 148 articles specifically using the term ‘spending over £500’ between May 2010 and August 2012 (though it is possible many journalists using the data did not mention the source</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> in their article</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">). The spending data was used to question authorities, focusing on odd spending at small level (air fresheners, taxis) or for individual councillors. Newspapers also urged the public to use the data and berated authorities that were slow or ‘lagging’ behind in publication. A selection of newspapers reported it more heavily where the spending data was causing particular controversy.  </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">6.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">NGOs heavily use FOI, often as part of wider campaigns alongside other instruments such as attending meetings, writing to councillors etc. It is possible national groups (such as the Taxpayers’ Alliance, mentioned in the surveys) and local activists are using the data in a similar way.   </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">6.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The biggest user group was business. Businesses are also big users of FOI at local level, from small ‘one person’ companies to multi-nationals</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref17"></a><a href="#_ftn17">[17]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> A 2010 study of data.gov.uk found a wide use by businesses and social entrepreneurs alongside IT innovators.</span><a name="_ftnref18"></a><a href="#_ftn18">[18]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Armchair Auditors</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">One of the most eye-catching ideas from the government’s Transparency Agenda is that of the ‘Armchair Auditor’ where citizens use newly ‘opened up’ information on spending, contracts and crime to hold public bodies to account. But has it happened</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">?</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 35.7pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">7.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Adrian Short has created open access software taken up by Auditors in the ‘North’ (Hull and Lincolnshire) and on the Isle of Wight. In London one particularly high profile case led to Eric Pickles publicly praising Armchair Auditors in their fight against Barnet’s ‘easycouncil’. But there are few signs of a wider </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">‘army’</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 35.7pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">7.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The first and most obvious </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">reason</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> is that the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> information is not yet consistent</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> so questioning and understanding it is not easy or possible. The Armchair Auditor also needs to be a particular type of person:  engaged and interested in local government, with </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">a </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">good grasp of ho</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">w government works and motivation and skills</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> to dedicate time to it. To have all these t</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">raits in combination is rare. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 35.7pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">7.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">A further</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> issue is how to use the information is used. The data is likely to work alongside other accountability tools - the activists in Barnet used a combination of FOI requests, the local media and judicial review.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> It is not yet clear where exactly ‘Armchair Audit’ fits. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 35.7pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">7.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Armchair Auditors, like all accountability mechanisms, work best in certain situations. A high profile scandal, as in Barnet, appears </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to be one way of kick starting audit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">. Auditors have appeared in particular situations, normally ‘accountability vacuums’, where there is no existing accountability or ‘formal’ mechanisms have failed. Given these limitations and the general difficulty of ‘crowd-sourcing’ </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">audit </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">is</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> likely to re</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">main limited</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">. The idea</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> behind audit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> indicates one of the misunderstandings about data - it is not ‘power’ by itself: it requires narrative and explanation and, most importantly, like FOI, it needs to work with other tools to bring </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">about </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">accountability.</span><a name="_ftnref19"></a><a href="#_ftn19">[19]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How successful has the Government’s Open Data initiative been in changing behaviour in the Civil Service and wider public sector? </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">8.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Measuring any behaviour change is difficult, especially as Open Data is so new. The real benefits are likely to arrive in the future, when joined up data and innovations can offer targeted information.</span><a name="_ftnref20"></a><a href="#_ftn20">[20]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">8.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Internally, some authorities have recorded improved information flows. There may</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> also</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> be increased ‘internal’ accountability as officials and politicians use the data to monitor </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">activity from within. Some authorities </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">reporting </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">us</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> the new data internally but it was not </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">clear what</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> for. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">8.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">There may also be better spending behaviour and professionalising of systems as a result of being ‘watched’. This again is difficult to measure but supported by some academic studies. Interviewees felt publishing spending data may either professionalise or drive ‘poor’ behaviour deeper underground. The exact effects would be dependent on how much the data</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> is being used (and its quality</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">) - the current low levels would be likely to have a small effect</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref21"></a><a href="#_ftn21">[21]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">8.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Open Data holds tremendous opportunities for policy-making. Interviewees pointed out that an emphasis on how information could be used in policy-making would improve its reception and significant</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ly alter</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> how policy </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">is</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> made and resources targeted, especially if joined up.  From small scale issues e.g. saving money through prescriptions to targeting homelessness or health resources, it can have a transformative impact.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">8.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">However, the lack of clarity over the aims makes it a difficult policy to persuade others to support. The danger is that, in times of scarce resources and growing pressure, senior officials would be unwilling to release data.  There may also be limitations due to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the lack of technical </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">skills.</span><a name="_ftnref22"></a><a href="#_ftn22">[22]</a></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">8.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The failure of data.gov</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> in the US</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> may serve as a l</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">esson, weakened by </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">a vicious cycle of a lack of co-operation from departments, eager to preserve current data for use in spending battles, and a lack of public use and interest.</span><a name="_ftnref23"></a><a href="#_ftn23">[23]</a></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">8.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">A final concern was that the spending data was a ‘political’ tool to help control local authorities and portray them as ‘reckless’ spenders</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> who were</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> ‘wasting’ money. This reflects a wider concern that the Open Data may be a ‘Trojan horse’ for privatisation by offering information to private providers.</span><a name="_ftnref24"></a><a href="#_ftn24">[24]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Which data is most useful?</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">9.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Research from FOI points towards a mismatch between what government hopes the public will be interested in and what data the public want. Aside from the high profile scandals, most requesters use FOI to obtain information of value to themselves and their </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">own lives: a form of ‘micro-political’ or ‘non-political’ use</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref25"></a><a href="#_ftn25">[25]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> This may be reflected in open data use. The most frequently downloaded data on data.gov concerns ‘core’ data useful for </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">broader </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">analysis or quotidian information. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">10</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">What type of transparency information is of most interest to users? </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">       </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The table below is drawn from the survey. Officials were asked what type of data was of most interest. The findings are interesting given the low interest in the spending data.  </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><div style="text-align:center"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin:0 auto"><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:133pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Type of data</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:49.6pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Number</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:42.55pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">%</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:133pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Spending data</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">              </span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:49.6pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">22</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:42.55pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">40</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:133pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Service performance</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">data</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:49.6pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">1</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:42.55pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">2</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:133pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Contracts</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:49.6pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">6</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:42.55pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">11</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:133pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Land and property </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">assets</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:49.6pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">1</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:42.55pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">2</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:133pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Other</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:49.6pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">24</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:42.55pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">49</span></p></td></tr></table></div><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">10.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Underneath this headline interest, respondents</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> used the ‘other’ category to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> list a wide variety of information, much of it ‘low-level’ or ‘micro-political’ matters including Council Tax and Business Rate statistics, Public Health Funeral data, Credit balances on NNDR accounts, car parking data, Senior Staff Salary Data, Planning Applications data. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Some of this is ‘quotidian’ data of the type seen in the table in section 6 above. </span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">What are the best examples of data being made open</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">?</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">A model for the joined up and simple approach is </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Openly Local</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">an interactive merging of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">democratic and financial data </span><a href="http://openlylocal.com/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://openlylocal.com/</span></a><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline"> . </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Other innovations could bring easy comparability such as </span><a href="http://www.appgov.org/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.appgov.org/</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> (note-this site is currently in the development stages) </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">An international </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">example </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">of a local a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">uthority </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">he City of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Toronto’s</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> 311 system</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><a href="http://www.toronto.ca/311/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.toronto.ca/311/</span></a><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline"> </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration:none">September 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-align:right; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">1</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 17.85pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> According to the Google definition: </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">visits</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">represent the number of individual sessions initiated by all the visitors to a site. A</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">pageview</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">is defined as a view of a page on your site</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">If a visitor clicks reload after reaching the page, this is counted as an additional pageview’</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">. A </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">hit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> is a general term for any activity recorded. see</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/1257084?hl=en-GB"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/1257084?hl=en-GB</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> Local Government Association (2012) </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">LGA Transparency Survey</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.local.gov.uk/c/document_library/get_file?uuid=bfad418d-1be8-43c8-bb9a-40faf3d41b82&amp;groupId=10171"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.local.gov.uk/c/document_library/get_file?uuid=bfad418d-1be8-43c8-bb9a-40faf3d41b82&amp;groupId=10171</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> Yu, Harlan, an